I would suggest strongly against this.  Do you have a magelo link?  If your wisdom is under 200, then this is worth it.  If it isn't, you will get more mana chosing other AA's.  Resist gear is for switching out for raids not for full time use usually - get levels and your resists take care of themselves against xp mobs.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Mental Clarity III. This is the first archetype I plan on practicing. The extra mana regeneration will be wonderful.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Mental Clarity 1 is definately worth two points.  There is a debate among clerics if MC2 is worth four points.  Almost every cleric agrees that MC3 is a waste of six points.  It isn't 2 points per level, it is 2+4+6 so 12 points by the time you get to MC3.  Get MC1 but then I would move on to the next thing on your list and come back for MC2 and possibly MC3 later if you decide you want them.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Healing Gift III. It's a prerequisite to many cleric archetypes. I'm not sure when I'll practice this one, 5 and 6 below are also very attractive.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
You will need it eventually and the occasional crit is nice.  Not really a big deal though unless you want a class skill for which this is a prerequisite.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Spell Casting Mastery. Anything to reduce fizzles. Fizzling a complete heal may mean the difference between a tank living and dying.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
This is the best cleric AA you can get before level 61.  It will give you WAY more mana then the extra wisdom.  I read the cleric board and I don't think there is a cleric there that wouldn't agree that this is a must have.  I would suggest pushing this up your list to the first arch skill you get but at very least suggest pushing it up to right after MC1.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Spell Casting Reinforcement. Getting a little more out of buffs is very important.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
This is nice because it also works on your heal over time spells.  I think you need to be at level three for it to give you an extra tick but I'm not positive.  <br>
<br>
Another thing to keep in mind, AAs are important but level helps you a lot as well.  Now that you have run3, you might want to consider pushing ahead to 60 and then stopping there to get the AAs instead of slowing down your advance to 60 for them.  Of course that depends on the level of the people you group with and where you hunt, but you do get more mana and better resists with each level so don't neglect levels and new spells for the AAs.   <p>[65 Archon] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=231627">Ariene</a> (High Elf) Bristlebane<BR>
