<br>
I see the opinion seems to be against spending AA on extra wisdom, but considering the ability to raise mana past 255 with PoP abilities, I think that this could be useful.  As well, I do not often have KEI. Nobody in my guild can cast it yet, and I don't have the funds to always pay for it. Also, seeing as I have to spend 6 AA in the general skills anyway, I thought I would go this route.  <br>
<br>
I've also been thinking about First Aid instead of extra wisdom, but I haven't decided yet.<br>
<br>
I also do not plan on leveling quickly, so saving up a large portion of AA points between now and level 60 is not a concern for me.  I have no desire to push towards level 60. There is still too much &quot;50s content&quot; that I have yet to see.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=azhreihieverdphlith>Azhrei Hiever dPhlith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Punter of Gnomes<br>Stealer of Dorfpickles<br>Master of Apep<br>ManWithReallyLongTitle</span><br>  Posts: 334<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/25/03 9:15:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=89.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cleric Alternate Advancement discussion</span><hr size=1> You don't need to be in a raiding guild to cap your wisdom, its remarkably easy to do.  My wisdom is over 283 (13+ points over my current cap of 270), with most of my gear being focused at mana gear and not wisdom gear, and with many of the things being obtainable either through question or through small (1 - 3 group) encounters.   Putting points into AA wisdom is a waste IMO, because you will find that once you have got that wisdom over cap, your focus will turn to straight +mana gear, and there is very few pieces of good +mana gear that don't also have solid wisdom bonuses.<br>
<br>
If your goal is resists, you would be better off spending those same points in AA resists so that you can keep your gear focused on mana.   Run3 is a definate, I prefer Regen3 as well but putting those three points on magic would be +6 RM. *shrug*   Spell Casting Mastery 3 should be the first set of AA's you get after, as SCM is the single biggest mana boost you can get for yourself. (My mana pool is roughly 4175, with SCM that pool is &quot;increased&quot; to effectively 5400, a boost of well over 1k mana, or effectively a 30% increase in mana pool).<br>
<br>
Every single thing you go for after SCM is entirely dependant on your playstyle.   Like to play battlecleric?  Go with casting fury for the nuke crits and hammer proc crits.  Stricktly a healing cleric?  Go for healing gift and adept.   Use the elixier series more often than direct healing?   Look at spell casting reinforcement / reinforcement mastery to extend the duration of the heal over time.  I agree with Tal,  putting 2 points in the first set of MC is a solid investment, anything beyond that depends on how desperate you are for mana regen.  Being in your mid 50's, there is multiple sources of flowing thought items you could group and / or get multi group events together for, IE 8th prayer shawl, slime boots. <p>Venerable Azhrei Hiever d'Phlith<br>
